Let’s say I have the following code on the pi:
NetworkTableEntry xEntry;
NetworkTableInstance inst = NetworkTableInstance.getDefault();
NetworkTable table = inst.getTable("datatable");
xEntry = table.getEntry("X");
inst.startClientTeam(5980);
On the rio, would simple writing public static NetworkTable table = NetworkTableInstance.getDefault().getTable("datatable"); get that same table on its end? Or do I need to start a server/put in a team number or something? Btw I’m using a network switch for comms between the roborio and pi
